  "abstract": {
    "value": "An efficient bimetallic Zn(II)/Cu(I)-mediated asymmetric synthesis of simple axially chiral allenes from terminal alkynes and aldehydes was realized by taking advantage of the chiral amine (S)-R,R-diphenylprolinol 3. This one-pot procedure is compatible with broad scopes of both terminal alkynes and aldehydes, providing axially chiral allenes in practical yields with an excellent enantioselectivity. Control experiments revealed that CuBr is responsible for the efficient formation of propargylic amine while the combination of CuBr and ZnBr plays crucial roles in the amine-to-allene transformation.",
